y.\n\n- Pooja\n|\nWhen the mind imagines its own lack of power, it is saddened by it.\n\n- Aleksandar Hemon, The Making of Zombie Wars\n|\nWow! It's like magic! she exclaimed.Simon shook his head. 'It's God's love. That's stronger than any magic.' - The Demon Trapper's Daughter\n\n- Jana\n|\nThis is generous, for to be close to her pain has always felt like a privilege to me, even though pain could be defined as that which we typically aim to avoid.\n\n- Maggie Nelson, Bluets\n|\nChange, like sunshine, can be a friend or a foe, a blessing or a curse, a dawn or a dusk.\n\n- William\n|\nIn light of heaven, the worst suffering on earth, a life full of the most atrocious tortures on earth, will be seen to be no more serious than one night in an inconvenient hotel.\n\n- Mother\n|\nLiterature is always personal, always one man's vision of the world, one man's experience, and it can only be popular when men are ready to welcome the visions of others.\n\n- W.B.\n|\nYour pain is trying to tell you something. It is not an accident, a curse, or an inconvenience. Pain is a form of self-communication.\n\n- Vironika\n|\nSelf-discipline, self-realization and self-reliance.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nCollectives can’t make money from virtues they make money from weakness. Where there are no weak, they create weak. Cowards hate strong people.\n\n- Moxie Will, Something That Will Change Your Life\n|\nIf there are finer beings than German short hairs, I don't know what they are. In their eyes is peace.\n\n- Ben\n|\nFrom someone who doesn't want to share your destiny, you should neither accept a cigarette\n\n- Cesare Pavese, The Burning Brand: Diaries, 1935-1950\n|\nA cat is friendly in a hollow sort of way, like the way a prostitute is friendly.\n\n- Jonathan-David Jackson, The Quest for Juice\n|\nLife is like a mirror.Cry and you see a crying face,Frown and you see a Sad Face !Smile and it smiles back at you !\n\n- Sham\n|\nBy acknowledging my imperma